Create a called Book with the following attributes:
title (string)
author (string)
isbn (string)
A method get_details() that returns a formatted string with all the book details.
Create a called BorrowedBook that inherits from the Book class. Add the following attributes:
borrower_name (string)
due_date (string)
A method get_borrow_details() that calls get_details() from the base class and adds the borrower details.
Write a program to create an instance of BorrowedBook and display its details.

Solution:

class Book {
     String title;
     String author;
     String isbn;

    public Book(String title, String author, String isbn) {
        this.title = title;
        this.author = author;
        this.isbn = isbn;
    }

    public String getDetails() {
        return "Title: " + title + "\nAuthor: " + author + "\nISBN: " + isbn;
    }
}

class BorrowedBook extends Book {
     String borrowerName;
     String dueDate;

    public BorrowedBook(String title, String author, String isbn, String borrowerName, String dueDate) {
        super(title, author, isbn); 
        this.borrowerName = borrowerName;
        this.dueDate = dueDate;
    }

    public String getBorrowDetails() {
        return getDetails() + "\nBorrower Name: " + borrowerName + "\nDue Date: " + dueDate;
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        BorrowedBook borrowedBook = new BorrowedBook(
            "Discrete Mathematics and its Applications",
            "kenneth H.Rosen",
            "9780073383095",
            "Asma",
            "2025-02-20"
        );

        System.out.println(borrowedBook.getBorrowDetails());
    }
